The family of Rev. Tunde Lemo, the former Deputy Governor of Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), has announced the death of their matriarch, Mrs. Eunice Olufolake Lemo. A statement by Mr. Lemo said Mrs. Lemo died on Wednesday. She was 85. A devout Christian and a staunch community leader, Mrs. Lemo is survived by children and grand-children who have made their marks in various fields of endeavor. The details of the celebration of her life will be communicated at a later date. 